        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(webchat): surface Codex commentary progress",
        "body": "## Summary\n- project Codex app-server `item/preamble` progress events into the WebChat transient chat stream\n- tag progress-only streams so final/aborted materialization does not persist commentary as assistant history\n- clarify Telegram docs: tool progress is default, Codex preamble/commentary requires `streaming.progress.commentary`\n\n## Trace\n- PR #89505 is merged into the latest release, but it only covered the ACP parent-stream path.\n- The default Codex app-server harness already emits commentary as `stream: \"item\"`, `kind: \"preamble\"` progress events.\n- Telegram on current main already routes those preamble events through `createChannelProgressDraftCompositor`, gated by `streaming.progress.commentary`.\n- WebChat was still ignoring `item/preamble` agent events, so runs could appear silent until final/tool output.\n\n## Tests\n- `pnpm vitest run ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts src/channels/progress-draft-compositor.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts`\n",
